              "long_description": "ODH's dashboard states that 'some data may be unavailable if fewer than ten cases are reported over the chosen timeframe.' During development, this county x week extraction was tested extensively (single-digit county counts, and statewide annual totals as low as 1-7 cases, were all returned by the source without being hidden), and no suppression was observed to occur at this specific resolution (county map, no age/sex/race breakdown). This column is always 0 in the current extraction and is retained for DCF schema compliance and so that if suppression is later observed (e.g. if the pipeline is extended to a demographic breakdown), imputed rows can be flagged consistently with other PopHIVE sources.",
