        "location_url": "https://analytics.das.ohio.gov/t/ODHDPPUB/views/GeneralCaseCountPublicPROD/GeographicalDistribution",
        "description": "Public dashboard launched March 2024 covering 100+ reportable infectious diseases in Ohio back to 2001, updated on a rolling basis (daily/weekly). Filterable by county, timeframe, age, sex, race, and ethnicity through the live dashboard UI; this ingest queries the dashboard's underlying Tableau Server view directly via its CSV crosstab export endpoint, setting the 'Reportable Condition' quick filter to Cyclosporiasis and the 'p_startdate'/'p_enddate' date parameters to each Sunday-Saturday week in turn, to obtain true county x week resolution. Non-perinatal hepatitis B, hepatitis C, HIV/AIDS, sexually transmitted diseases, and tuberculosis are excluded from this dashboard by ODH and are not part of this pipeline. ODH states that some data may be unavailable when fewer than ten cases are reported over a chosen timeframe, though this was not observed to affect the specific county-map view used here (see suppressed_flag notes).",
